-- Raspadskaya Slides to Three-Week Low as Share Buyback Closes
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-01-31T13:45:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/raspadskaya-slides-to-three-week-low-as-share-buyback-closes.html
OAO Raspadskaya (RASP) , a Russian coal
miner, fell to its lowest level in almost three weeks as the
company stopped accepting bids for a share buyback.  The stock dropped 0.8 percent to 106.15 rubles as of 5:36
p.m. in Moscow, headed for it weakest close since Jan. 12.  Raspadskaya (RASP)  is aiming to buy back as much as 10 percent of
its stock for 150 rubles a share. The company stopped accepting
bids to repurchase the shares at 2 p.m. in Moscow today,
according to its press-office. The results of the buyback are
due to be announced by Feb. 7.  Steelmaker Evraz Plc and Raspadskayaâ€™s management jointly
control 80 percent of the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
